ce:section.ce:para:
In previous sections, the development and recent advances of different types of SSE (β-alumina, NASICON, sulfide-based, complex hydrides, and organic electrolyte) for Na batteries and concomitant interface issues have been overviewed. To achieve a better understanding of this field, we summarize the strategies (Figure 10
                           ) toward improving the performance of SSE, including ionic conductivity, transference number, chemical/electrochemical stability, mechanical property, and interface issues (interfacial contact and chemical compatibility). In addition, the main performance, advantages, and disadvantages of different types of representative SSE are also provided in Table 1
                           .
